  "response": "To qualify for AARP membership, you need to be at least **50 years old**. However, AARP also offers a special membership category called \"Associate Membership\" for those under 50 who are interested in joining. Associate Members receive many of the same benefits as regular members but are not eligible for certain age-restricted programs or services. If you're 50 or older, you can become a full AARP member and access all the benefits and resources they offer.",
